Findings
Research in agricultural entrepreneurship has performed well in terms of publication volume and impact, with a broad range of contributors from various authors, journals and countries. The key themes in this research field include entrepreneurial capacity in agriculture, rural development through agricultural entrepreneurship, social entrepreneurship for rural empowerment, technological innovation in agribusiness, youth engagement in agricultural entrepreneurship, urban agricultural entrepreneurship for food security. These themes are timely and relevant, as they reflect agriculture’s response to global challenges including climate change, rural unemployment, digital disruption and post-Covid economic landscape. The review also highlights that agricultural entrepreneurship is no longer confined to traditional farm-based models, but now incorporates innovation ecosystems, digital platforms and inclusive business models, offering a broader theoretical perspective and reflecting recent empirical developments.
